Olufemi Olaniyi, Ibadan There was confusion in Okeho in the Kajola Local Government Area of Oyo State on Wednesday as armed robbers reportedly attacked a bank in the town. The robbers were reportedly engaged by some hunters and three of the assailants were said to have been caught and set ablaze by residents of the town. [READ ALSO] 2020 NECO exams start Oct 5 The Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Olugbenga Fadeyi, confirmed the incident to our correspondent. He, however, said he was still gathering information about the attack and would revert later.